descr: "Describes the intention of how one or more practitioners intend to deliver care for a particular patient, group or community for a period of time, possibly limited to care for a specific condition or set of conditions."

fields.name: outcomeCodeableConcept
fields.descr: "Identifies the outcome at the point when the status of the activity is assessed.  For example, the outcome of an education activity could be patient understands (or not)."

fields.name: outcomeReference
fields.descr: "Details of the outcome or action resulting from the activity.  The reference to an \"event\" resource, such as Procedure or Encounter or Observation, is the result/outcome of the activity itself.  The activity can be conveyed using CarePlan.activity.detail OR using the CarePlan.activity.reference (a reference to a “request” resource)."

fields.name: progress
fields.descr: "Notes about the adherence/status/progress of the activity."

fields.name: reference
fields.descr: "The details of the proposed activity represented in a specific resource."

fields.name: detail
fields.descr: "A simple summary of a planned activity suitable for a general care plan system (e.g. form driven) that doesn't know about specific resources such as procedure etc."
